Key Match Events: The Bucks were blown out by the Knicks, losing 116-94, with Giannis Antetokounmpo scoring 24 points and 12 rebounds.
Post-Match Reflections: Giannis Antetokounmpo expressed frustration with the team's effort, saying they didn't 'compete' and calling out their performance.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks' 2-7 record is tied with the Toronto Raptors for the third-worst mark in the NBA.
Others: Giannis Antetokounmpo struggled from the free-throw line, going 2-of-6 from the charity stripe and lowering his success rate for the season to a career-low 54.9 percent on 10.3 attempts per game.
